claim.claim-text:
1. An equipped hub of an exhaust casing comprising:
a hub center;
an upstream flange disposed on an upstream side of the hub center;
a downstream flange disposed on a downstream side of the hub center; and
a plurality of cuffs extending radially from the hub center and arranged circumferentially around the hub center,
wherein at least one rib is provided at an exterior of a base of each cuff so as to surround the cuff below a maximum stress location in the cuff, said rib being joined to the downstream flange at a downstream end of the rib and to the upstream flange at an upstream end of the rib.
